  "prompt": "What are things one should be looking at while buying a second hand car?",
  "response": "When buying a second-hand car, consider the following:\n\n1. Mechanical Condition\n- Engine condition\n- Transmission\n- Suspension\n- Brake system\n- Exhaust system\n- Oil leaks\n- Tire condition\n\n2. Vehicle History\n- Accident history\n- Number of previous owners\n- Maintenance records\n- Service history\n- Mileage verification\n- Vehicle identification number (VIN) check\n\n3. Exterior Inspection\n- Body condition\n- Paint quality\n- Rust spots\n- Dents and scratches\n- Panel alignment\n- Windshield and window condition\n\n4. Interior Condition\n- Seat condition\n- Dashboard functionality\n- Air conditioning\n- Electronics and controls\n- Carpet and upholstery\n- Signs of wear and tear\n\n5. Documentation\n- Registration papers\n- Insurance history\n- Clear title\n- No outstanding loans\n\n6. Test Drive\n- Driving performance\n- Noise levels\n- Steering alignment\n- Brake responsiveness\n- Acceleration\n- Gear shifting\n\n7. Additional Checks\n- Battery condition\n- Electrical systems\n- Warning lights\n- Professional inspection by a mechanic\n- Get vehicle history report\n\n8. Price Comparison\n- Market value\n- Comparable models\n- Negotiation potential",
